I'll design a simple n8n workflow: **Weekly AI Open Source Brief** — cron-triggered, fetches trending AI repos from GitHub, compiles a markdown brief, emails it, saves to Drive, with full error handling and review queue.

**Workflow name:** Weekly AI Open Source Brief

**Trigger:** Cron — Mondays 08:00 America/New_York

**Data flow:**

1. Cron → 2. Set run_id (function) → 3. Fetch GitHub repos (HTTP) → 4. Check response → 5. Generate brief (function) → 6. Send email (Gmail) → 7. Upload to Drive → 8. Log success (Sheets)

**Error handling:** All external nodes (HTTP, Gmail, Drive, Sheets) have `continueOnFail: true` and route errors to a unified Error Handler that writes to a Review Queue (Sheets) and sends an alert email.

**Idempotency:** Briefs are saved with date-based filenames; duplicate runs on same day overwrite. For stricter idempotency, add a dedup lookup before generation.

**Retries:** Exponential backoff (3 attempts) on all network calls.

**Credentials needed:** `GITHUB_TOKEN`, `GMAIL_CRED`, `DRIVE_CRED`, `SHEETS_CRED`, plus sheet IDs and Drive folder ID.

Here is the importable n8n workflow JSON:

```json
{
  "name": "Weekly AI Open Source Brief",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "name": "Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.cron",
      "id": "trigger",
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "cronExpression",
              "value": "0 8 * * 1"
            }
          ]
        },
        "timezone": "America/New_York"
      },
      "position": [240, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Set Run ID",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "id": "set-run-id",
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "const runId = $now.format('YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss') + '-' + $input.all()[0].json.id;\nitems[0].json.run_id = runId;\nitems[0].json.run_timestamp = new Date().toISOString();\nreturn items;"
      },
      "position": [460, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Fetch GitHub Repos",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "id": "fetch-github",
      "parameters": {
        "url": "https://api.github.com/search/repositories",
        "method": "GET",
        "queryParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "q", "value": "ai+open+source+language:python" },
            { "name": "sort", "value": "stars" },
            { "name": "order", "value": "desc" },
            { "name": "per_page", "value": "10" }
          ]
        },
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "headerAuth": {
          "name": "Authorization",
          "value": "Bearer {{ $env.GITHUB_TOKEN }}"
        },
        "options": {
          "timeout": 30000,
          "retry": {
            "enabled": true,
            "maxTries": 3,
            "waitBetween": "exponentialBackoff",
            "minWait": 1000,
            "maxWait": 10000
          }
        }
      },
      "position": [680, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Check Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "id": "check-response",
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": { "caseSensitive": true, "typeValidation": "strict" },
          "conditions": [
            {
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.status }}",
              "rightValue": "200",
              "operator": { "type": "string", "operation": "equals" }
            }
          ],
          "combinator": "and"
        }
      },
      "position": [900, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Generate Brief",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "id": "generate-brief",
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "const items = $input.all();\nif (items.length === 0) throw new Error('No items received');\nconst data = items[0].json;\nconst repos = data.items || [];\nconst briefDate = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\nlet md = `# Weekly AI Open Source Brief - ${briefDate}\\n\\n`;\nmd += `Total repositories: ${repos.length}\\n\\n`;\nmd += '| Repository | Stars | Language | Description |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n';\nfor (const repo of repos) {\n  md += `| [${repo.full_name}](${repo.html_url}) | ${repo.stargazers_count} | ${repo.language || 'N/A'} | ${repo.description || ''} |\\n`;\n}\nitems[0].json.brief = md;\nitems[0].json.brief_date = briefDate;\nreturn items;"
      },
      "position": [1120, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Send Email",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmail",
      "id": "send-email",
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "send",
        "to": "team@example.com",
        "subject": "Weekly AI Open Source Brief - {{ $json.brief_date }}",
        "message": "{{ $json.brief }}",
        "sendTo": "to",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "googleOAuth2"
      },
      "position": [1340, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Upload to Drive",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleDrive",
      "id": "upload-drive",
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "create",
        "fileName": "ai-brief-{{ $json.brief_date }}.md",
        "folderId": "{{ $env.BRIEFS_FOLDER_ID }}",
        "fileContent": "{{ $json.brief }}",
        "mimeType": "text/markdown",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "googleOAuth2",
        "options": {
          "retry": {
            "enabled": true,
            "maxTries": 3,
            "waitBetween": "exponentialBackoff",
            "minWait": 1000,
            "maxWait": 10000
          }
        }
      },
      "position": [1560, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Log Success",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets",
      "id": "log-success",
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "append",
        "sheetId": "{{ $env.LOG_SHEET_ID }}",
        "columns": {
          "mappingMode": "defineBelow",
          "value": {
            "run_id": "{{ $json.run_id }}",
            "status": "success",
            "timestamp": "{{ $json.run_timestamp }}",
            "brief_date": "{{ $json.brief_date }}"
          }
        },
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "googleOAuth2",
        "options": {
          "retry": {
            "enabled": true,
            "maxTries": 3,
            "waitBetween": "exponentialBackoff",
            "minWait": 1000,
            "maxWait": 10000
          }
        }
      },
      "position": [1780, 300]
    },
    {
      "name": "Error Handler",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "id": "error-handler",
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "const errorItem = $input.item(\"0\");\nconst error = {\n  run_id: errorItem.json.run_id || 'N/A',\n  node: errorItem.node?.name || 'unknown',\n  error_message: errorItem.json?.message || String(errorItem.json),\n  stack_trace: errorItem.json?.stack || '',\n  timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n};\nreturn [{ json: error }];"
      },
      "position": [1000, 600]
    },
    {
      "name": "Write Review Queue",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets",
      "id": "write-review",
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "append",
        "sheetId": "{{ $env.REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_ID }}",
        "columns": {
          "mappingMode": "defineBelow",
          "value": {
            "run_id": "{{ $json.run_id }}",
            "failed_node": "{{ $json.node }}",
            "error_message": "{{ $json.error_message }}",
            "stack_trace": "{{ $json.stack_trace }}",
            "timestamp": "{{ $json.timestamp }}"
          }
        },
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "googleOAuth2"
      },
      "position": [1220, 600]
    },
    {
      "name": "Alert Email",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.gmail",
      "id": "alert-email",
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "send",
        "to": "admin@example.com",
        "subject": "❌ n8n workflow failed: {{ $json.run_id }}",
        "message": "Workflow **Weekly AI Open Source Brief** failed at node **{{ $json.failed_node }}**.\\n\\nError: {{ $json.error_message }}\\n\\nCheck review queue: {{ $env.REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_URL }}",
        "sendTo": "to",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "googleOAuth2"
      },
      "position": [1440, 600]
    }
  ],
  "connections": {
    "Trigger": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "set-run-id", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "set-run-id": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "fetch-github", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "fetch-github": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "check-response", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "check-response": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "generate-brief", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "generate-brief": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "send-email", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "send-email": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "upload-drive", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "upload-drive": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "log-success", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "log-success": {
      "main": [[]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "error-handler", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "error-handler": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "write-review", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "write-review": {
      "main": [[{ "node": "alert-email", "type": "main", "index": 0 }]],
      "error": [[{ "node": "alert-email", "type": "error", "index": 0 }]]
    },
    "alert-email": {
      "main": [[]],
      "error": [[]]
    }
  },
  "settings": {
    "executionOrder": "v1"
  },
  "active": false
}
```

**Runbook (`runbook.md`):**

```markdown
# Weekly AI Open Source Brief — Runbook

## Purpose
Automatically generate a weekly brief of trending AI/ML open-source repositories from GitHub and distribute it via email and Google Drive.

## Schedule
- **Trigger:** Cron
- **Expression:** `0 8 * * 1` (Mondays at 08:00)
- **Timezone:** America/New_York

## Data Contract
- **Input:** None (workflow generates its own data)
- **Output:** Markdown file `ai-brief-YYYY-MM-DD.md` saved to Drive folder; email sent to `team@example.com`.

## Idempotency
- Briefs are saved with date-based filenames; re-running on the same day overwrites the previous file.
- For stricter idempotency, maintain a "ProcessedRepos" sheet keyed by `repo.full_name + brief_date` and skip duplicates.

## Error Handling & Retries
- All external nodes (HTTP Request, Gmail, Google Drive, Google Sheets) use exponential backoff retries (3 attempts).
- Unhandled errors are routed to the **Error Handler**, which writes a record to the Review Queue and sends an alert email to `admin@example.com`.
- No node is allowed to fail silently (`continueOnFail: true` on all external nodes).

## Human-in-the-Loop Review Queue
- Failed runs are logged in the **Review Queue** Google Sheet (ID: `REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_ID`). Columns: `run_id`, `failed_node`, `error_message`, `stack_trace`, `timestamp`.
- Operators can manually re-process a failed run by copying the `run_id` into a reprocess interface (to be built separately).

## Monitoring & Alerts
- Successes are logged in the **Execution Log** Google Sheet (`LOG_SHEET_ID`) with `run_id`, `status`, `timestamp`, `brief_date`.
- Alert emails include a direct link to the review queue (set `REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_URL` env var).

## Required Credentials & Environment Variables
| Name | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GitHub API token (public repo read access) |
| `GMAIL_CRED` | n8n Google OAuth2 credential for sending email |
| `DRIVE_CRED` | n8n Google OAuth2 credential for Drive upload |
| `SHEETS_CRED` | n8n Google OAuth2 credential for Sheets access |
| `BRIEFS_FOLDER_ID` | Google Drive folder ID to store briefs |
| `LOG_SHEET_ID` | Google Sheet ID for success log |
| `REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_ID` | Google Sheet ID for failure queue |
| `REVIEW_QUEUE_SHEET_URL` | Direct URL to review queue sheet (for alert links) |

All credentials must be created in n8n's **Credentials** UI and referenced by the names above.

## Maintenance
- Verify token scopes monthly.
- Archive old briefs from Drive after 90 days.
- Rotate the GitHub token every 6 months.

## Troubleshooting
If the workflow fails repeatedly:
1. Check the review queue sheet for error details.
2. Validate that all environment variables and credential names are correct.
3. Ensure the GitHub token has not exceeded rate limits.
4. Test each external node individually using n8n's "Execute Node" feature.
```

You can now import the JSON into n8n (`Workflows → Import`) and configure the required credentials/environment variables. The workflow will run automatically every Monday at 8 AM and produce the brief.
